<br>
&quot;Ah...here are the reinforcements.&quot;<br>
<br>
::Then pointed in Ares direction as the cobalts charged hacking and slashing at the army in front of them::<br>
<br>
::Mojo then drew the axe from his back.  The enormous double bladed battle axe, forged magically by Hephaestus himself.  A glare of red crossed Mojo's eyes as the axe began glowing and humming with magical power.  It would take someone with nearly the strength of a Titan or a God to wield such an axe.  Mojo inherited that strength from his Titan grandfather.  He then pointed towards Dionysus and his &quot;brood&quot; as another couple of hundred cobalts rose from the ground and attacked the centaurs::<br>
<br>
::Mojo with his enormous strength and the cobalts, cut through the most of the small army of centaurs like hot butter until he could get to the catapults.  Using the blade of his axe he systematically cut the ropes on each of the catapults, essentially making all of them useless.  Allowing the cobalts to fight it out with the centaurs, he slowly walked over to Dionysus.  He knew better than to strike a god since he himself was not one.  He set the axe head on the ground holding onto the handle showing he would not attack him::<br>
<br>
&quot;Dionysus...You are not a war god.  Therefore I SUGGEST you step off the battlefield, for it is not your domain.  I know better than to strike or attack you personally, but that same respect is not extended to that 'army' you brought with you.  Therefore I suggest you lead them off the field before they are all dead.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He then turns away from Dionysus and started hacking through the centaurs again, with his axe, gorging a few of them in their bodies with his large horns.  Once it looks as though the Cobalts are descimating and the centaurs are almost completely destroyed, he turns his attention to the front.  The place were Ares's army is:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=thegoddesshecate>The Goddess Hecate</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicon/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(8/7/01 9:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Fat Lady Hasn't Sung Yet...</span><hr size=1> :: looking to where Mojo stood from her charriot she smirks while dropping her reins and pointed both hands at him makes quick sand to form under his feet then  continues to put out all of the flames her facial features no more smiling or smirking::<br>
